==============================================================================================================
                                       Credit Card Report – Exploratory Data Analysis Project
==============================================================================================================


This is an end-to-end Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) project where I analyzed credit card customer and 
transaction data using Python (Pandas), MySQL, and Power BI.
I have created this project to practice the complete workflow of cleaning raw data, storing it in a database, 
and building dashboards to generate insights.


Project Workflow
-----------------

1. Data Processing (Python – Pandas)

* Loaded and cleaned CSV datasets
* Checked duplicates and formatted data
* Prepared datasets for database storage

2. Database Management (MySQL)

* Created tables for customer and credit card datasets
* Added Primary and Foreign Key relationships
* Converted date fields and performed joins for analysis

3. Data Visualization (Power BI)

* Built an interactive dashboard
* Analyzed customer demographics, revenue trends, and transaction patterns


Tools Used
-----------

Python (Pandas)
MySQL
Power BI
Jupyter Notebook


Project Structure
------------------

Credit-Card-EDA/
├── customer.csv
├── credit_card.csv
├── Cards.ipynb
├── cards.sql
└──  Cards_PowerBI.pbix


Skills Practiced
-----------------
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Data cleaning using Pandas
* SQL joins and database relationships
* Dashboard creation using Power BI

This project helped me understand how Python, MySQL, and Power BI work together in a data analytics workflow.

